api_list.name: Product
api_list.description:
The Product Parameters are applicable when making a request with `type=product` to retrieve details of a single product on Home Depot - the product is specified using either the item_id parameter or the url parameter (where the url parameter contains a link to a Home Depot product page). The parameters should be appended as querystring parameters to the Home Depot Product Data APIGETHTTP request.

Product details are retrieved from the product page for a single product on Home Depot

optional_parameters.name: gtin
optional_parameters.description: The GTIN/ISBN/UPC code to look up a matching product on Home Depot for. If the gtin parameter is supplied then the item_id parameter is ignored. GTIN-based requests work by looking up the GTIN/ISBN/UPC on Home Depot first, then retrieving the product details for the first matching item_id.

optional_parameters.name: url
optional_parameters.description:
The Home Depot product-page URL to retrieve product details from.

Use either `item_id` OR `url`. 

If the item_id is included, do **NOT** include the URL

**Note: If the url parameter is supplied then the item_id and gtin parameters are ignored (the url overrides other parameters).**

optional_parameters.name: output
optional_parameters.description:
Determines the format in which results are returned: `JSON`, `HTML` or `CSV`

JSON is the default

optional_parameters.name: item_id
optional_parameters.description: The Home Depot Item ID to retrieve product details for.

feature_bullets: Includes 40V 6.0 Ah Battery and a Fast Charger
3-in-1 Capable Right Out of the Box
product.description: RYOBI continues to lead the industry in cordless mower innovation with their 40V HP 20" Brushless Push Mower. Combining 40V Lithium Battery power with Brushless Technology this mower delivers GAS PERFORMANCE, without the hassle of gas, oil, or maintenance. The high capacity 6Ah battery provides extended run time and instant power at the push of a button. With the 3-in-1 mowing functions you can choose between bagging, mulching, or side discharge functions right out of the box. Select your ideal grass height with the 7-position single point height adjustment. The easy lift bag removal allows you to quickly and easily empty the grass catcher bag and get back to work. With folding handles, this mower easily folds down when the job is done and can be stored vertically making it ideal for compact spaces. Not only is this mower equipped with a 40V 6Ah battery, but also a 40V Fast Charger for 2X faster charging. As part of the RYOBI 40V system, it is compatible with all 40V batteries. The 40V HP 20" Brushless Push Mower is backed by a 5-year tool warranty.

api_list.name: Reviews
api_list.description:
The Reviews Parameters are applicable when making a request with `type=reviews` to retrieve customer Reviews for a single product on Home Depot - the product is specified using either the item_id or url parameter (where the url parameter contains a link to a Home Depot product page). The parameters should be appended as querystring parameters to the Home Depot Product Data API GET HTTP request.

Reviews are retrieved from the customer reviews page for a single product on Home Depot.

required_parameters.name: item_id
required_parameters.description:
The Home Depot Item ID to retrieve Reviews for.

**Note: If the item_id parameter is supplied then the url parameter is ignored.**

optional_parameters.name: page
optional_parameters.description:
The current page of reviews to retrieve. Inspect the pagination.total_pages property in the Reviews results to see how many pages of reviews are available.

**Note the maximum number of reviews per page is 10 (this is a Home Depot limit).**

update value of num to get additional pages

optional_parameters.name: output
optional_parameters.description:
Determines the format in which results are returned: `JSON`, `HTML` or `CSV`

JSON is the default

optional_parameters.name: four_star
optional_parameters.description: Set to true to filter to only reviews that give the product a 4-star rating.

optional_parameters.name: sort_by
optional_parameters.description:
Determines the sort order of reviews to return. Valid values are:

- photo_reviews
- most_helpful
- newest_to_oldest
- oldest_to_newest
- high_to_low_rating
- low_to_high_rating

optional_parameters.name: reviewer_type
optional_parameters.description:
The type of reviewer to retrieve reviews from. Valid values are:

`verified_purchase` : Include reviews by Verified Purchasers only.
`all` : Include all reviews, regardless of whether they are from Verified Purchasers or not.

optional_parameters.name: gtin
optional_parameters.description: The GTIN/ISBN/UPC code to look up a matching product on Home Depot for to retrieve reviews for. If the gtin parameter is supplied then the `item_id` parameter is ignored. GTIN-based requests work by looking up the GTIN/ISBN/UPC on Home Depot first, then retrieving the reviews for the first matching `item_id`.

optional_parameters.name: two_star
optional_parameters.description: Set to true to filter to only reviews that give the product a 2-star rating.

optional_parameters.name: five_star
optional_parameters.description: Set to true to filter to only reviews that give the product a 5-star rating.

optional_parameters.name: one_star
optional_parameters.description: Set to true to filter to only reviews that give the product a 1-star rating.

optional_parameters.name: three_star
optional_parameters.description: Set to true to filter to only reviews that give the product a 3-star rating.

optional_parameters.name: search_term
optional_parameters.description: A search term to use to search reviews.

optional_parameters.name: url
optional_parameters.description: The Home Depot reviews-page URL to retrieve Reviews from.

reviews.title: Stopped working 4 months
reviews.body: I bought this mower for my small yard in retirement community.  Lasted 4 months charged battery now won’t start at all.  Going back to a gas mower more reliable.

reviews.title: 2nd Ryobi mower
reviews.body: I bought the 16 inch mower years ago to do the parts of my lawn the tractor couldn't reach. Gradually that became my primary mower because it was easier to use. I decided to upgrade to the 20 inch because it can cut a wider path. My 16 inch is still going strong and I expect that this 20 inch will be great for years to come.

reviews.title: Switched From Gas Mower in 2022 & Love This Thing!
reviews.body: I bought this model in May and found the cut equal to my old gas-engine mower. So far this autumn, I've used this mower twice to mulch the leaves in my backyard (see photo). Yes, I needed to tilt the mower onto its rear wheels at times and slowly lower it onto the pile, and I also had to make a few passes to really mulch the leaves up -- but I had to do both of those things with my gas-powered mower, too. VERY impressed with this model.

reviews.title: Terrible Battery Life
reviews.body: We bought this because it should be good to cut 1/2 an acre. We went and bought a second battery for near $200 so we could finish the small front yard. I’m only trying to cut 1/4 acre. The grass is not 10 foot tall. Day two both batteries charged and it cut a fraction of the backyard. It mulches great, but one small yard has taken an extra battery and two days and it’s still not done. Returning it today.

reviews.title: It does the job very well
reviews.body: excellent lawn mower.  need two batteries to cut 1/4 ac.  I recommend it to change the gas one for one of this.

reviews.title: Excellent mower
reviews.body: Fully satisfied with this mower. Lightweight, easy to use, powerful enough and battery longevity is enough to do my front and back yards and more. Love the three options, mulch, side, and bag. Height adjustment is a breeze. Charging is simple.

reviews.title: Mind blown
reviews.body: I bought this, initially I was sceptical as to how it would perform on my smallish lawn and so far I’m extremely pleased. It cuts beautifully and the bagging is amazing, I can’t see a stray blade of grass once I’m done. It performs well even in tall, moist grass and it is incredibly light and folds for storage. I usually mow from between 30-45 minutes and so far it hasn’t died on me. I’ve been singing the praises to my neighbours and one of them bought a size bigger and she is loving it too. Oh and the height adjustment is easy, and the battery charges pretty fast, like 3-4 hours from almost drained.

reviews.title: Good Mower, but ...
reviews.body: Bought this mower on May 2, 2022. I have a small yard (~450sq/ft). Strictly light duty. Everything was going great until last weekend (July 23) when I shift to change directions and the grass flap twists off. And by looking at the bend in the rod, I cannot understand how this could have possibly happened. The operational quality of the mower itself is actually quite impressive. Powerful, battery lasts a long time, lightweight, nice even cut ... and I love the vertical storage. But if all of the individual parts that make this thing are as flimsy and low quality as the grass flap, I'm wondering how long this machine will actually last. For now, I'll still give it a favourable rating, but I can't deny the disappointment in this simple piece breaking after only 3 months of light usage.

reviews.title: Easy to assemble, and the best lawnmower I’ve owne
reviews.body: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] My wife bought me this lawnmower for Father’s Day and I was thrilled. It’s very easy to assemble, very quiet, and the battery lasts a long time. It even folds for easy storage.

reviews.title: Much better than previous version
reviews.body: This version of the lawn mower is much better quality than the previous model. Start promptly, and it does feel built with cheap materials. The size of the mower is more compact so it's easier to cut corners and next to the wall. I recommend this mower to anyone who is switching from gas. It was easy to set up, I was cutting the lawn in less than 10 minutes. Seem that Ryobi has learned from the previous version to improve this mower. I had a cutoff issue with the previous version. The new version does not have this issue.

api_list.name: Category
api_list.description:
The Category Parameters are applicable when making a request with `type=category` to retrieve category results from Home Depot. The category is specified in the category_id parameter. The parameters should be appended as querystring parameters to the Home Depot Product Data API GET HTTP request.

Category results are retrieved from the Category results page on Home Depot.

required_parameters.name: category_id
required_parameters.description: A category ID to retrieve results from. You may supply any arbitary value in the category_id parameter however we recommend using a category ID returned from the Categories API as these are known-good category IDs from Home Depot.

optional_parameters.name: sort_by
optional_parameters.description:
Determines how the results are sorted. Valid values are:

- best_seller
- most_popular
- price_high_to_low
- price_low_to_high
- highest_rating

optional_parameters.name: output
optional_parameters.description:
Determines the format in which results are returned: `JSON`, `HTML` or `CSV`

JSON is the default

optional_parameters.name: max_price
optional_parameters.description: Determines the maximum price of results to return, expressed in dollars and cents (i.e. `min_price=39.99` for $39.99).

optional_parameters.name: min_price
optional_parameters.description: Determines the maximum price of results to return, expressed in dollars and cents (i.e. `min_price=39.99` for $39.99).

optional_parameters.name: page
optional_parameters.description:
The current page of results to retrieve. Inspect the pagination results property for details on the number of pages available.

update value of num to get additional pages

optional_parameters.name: url
optional_parameters.description:
The Home Depot category results page to retrieve results from.

**Note: If the url parameter is supplied then all other parameters are ignored as they are overriden be those specified in the url parameter.**

api_list.description:
The Search Parameters are applicable when making a request with `type=search` to retrieve search results from Home Depot. The search term is specified in the search_term parameter. The parameters should be appended as querystring parameters to the Home Depot Product Data API GET HTTP request.

Search results are retrieved from the Search results page on Home Depot.
